reviews.productTitle: Legrand Pass & Seymour 660WSLCC10 Trademaster 15 Amp Single Pole Illuminated Toggle Light Switch, Lighted When Off, Residential Grade, White (1 Count)
reviews.text: I like the brightness of the light. Some say it is too dim. They are missing the purpose. It is not intended to light up an area. It is intended to make it easy to see the switch in a dark room. It does that very well. It glows amber around the switch so you can see it easily. Installation was easy. The posts are offset. Commonly, you have both wires attach on the same side of a switch. On this, they are on opposite sides of the switch. But, that doesn't make it more difficult to install. If you don't know what you are doing, I strongly suggest getting a qualified electrician to install it. Electricity is dangerous. The problem I have is that this switch leaks. I use LED lights. They have a capacitor leading into the AC to DC circuit. The tiny bit of power leaking into the line charges up the capacitor. When it is charged, it quickly discharges and the LED light blinks. So, my lights blink, very quickly, about once a second. I grounded the switch to see if that would help. It didn't. I can get different lights, but I would rather have a switch that doesn't leak.
reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States on October 5, 2024
reviews.title: Almost perfect
